<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="R" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Rescue2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Rescue,</orth> vb. 1) to deliver by main force: <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 4.3.134" default="NO" valid="yes">As IV, 3, 134</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 3.2.239" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. III, 2, 239</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 5.53" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. V, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.2.7" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 2, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.104" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.364" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 364</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 1.4.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C I, 4, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.1.112" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 1, 112</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.1.176" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 1, 176</bibl>. With <cit><quote>from:</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 5.4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. V, 4, 21</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 6, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.5" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 5</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.6.5" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 6, 5</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.84" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 6, 84</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.49" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 49</bibl>. <cit><quote>--d the Black Prince from forth the ranks of many thousand French,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 3, 101</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) to save in any manner: <cit><quote>r. those breathing lives to die in beds,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 2.419" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 419</bibl></cit>. With <emph>from</emph>: <cit><quote>how well this yielding --s thee from shame,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>wouldst have me r. thee from this reproach,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.4.64" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 4, 64</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>unless thou r. him from foul despair,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.3.215" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 3, 215</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>